description:
Bug 38131: ajc needs -d option while correctly compiling classes from subpackage. I am using 1.1rc1. This is a regression since rc1 and a deviation from javac. I am guessing this may have something to do with a change in the underlying Eclipse compiler.

To reproduce the issue, follow these steps:

1. Create a class in a subpackage, for example:
   package subpackage;

   public class Test {
       public static void main(String[] args) {
           System.out.println("Hello");
       }
   }

2. Compile the class using the following command:
   ajc -d . subpackage\Test.java

Observed Behavior:
A directory named "subpackage" is created within the existing "subpackage" directory.

Expected Behavior:
The compiled class file should be placed in the existing "subpackage" directory, without creating a nested subdirectory.

Note: This behavior differs from the behavior of the javac compiler.
